The paper deals with network coding capacity in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of random geometric graphs and interference models suggests a focus on mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of coupling and martingale methods suggests a focus on probability and statistics (cs.DS).
